About Treasury Corporation of Victoria
Treasury Corporation of Victoria (TCV) is the central financial institution for the State of Victoria. Guided by its mission to raise capital and manage risk, TCV works to strengthen financial stability and resilience across the public sector for the benefit of the State, its clients and the broader Victorian community.

The Opportunity
Reporting to the Head of Sustainability, this role helps deliver the sustainability strategy by coordinating government-wide collaboration, supporting the sustainable finance program, engaging with stakeholders, and managing data analysis and reporting for internal and external communications. This is a full-time, 12-month fixed-term contract.

Key Responsibilities:

Assist the Head of Sustainability, members of the Treasury team, and senior leaders, as required, in the execution of TCV’s sustainability strategy;
Support the Head of Sustainability, members of the Treasury team, and senior leaders, as required, in investor relations activities and engagement with clients in relation to TCV’s sustainability strategy and sustainable financing program;
Liaise and collaborate with stakeholders across government to support delivery of the strategy and TCV’s sustainable debt issuance;
Assist in the governance, management and reporting in relation to TCV’s sustainable bonds framework, including identification and assessment of eligible expenditures, monitoring eligible expenditures, supporting asset pool modelling, gathering data for impact reporting, and assisting in the preparation of materials for the sustainable issuance committee;
Assist in the preparation of presentations, management, board and external reporting, and internal and external stakeholder communications in relation to sustainability;
Support the development and management of relationships with sustainable finance market participants, subject matter experts and industry bodies;
Proactively identify and research industry developments, market trends, and stakeholder expectations to support implementation of the strategy, embed best practice, educate clients and TCV employees, and enable ongoing issuance under the program;
Support and contribute on behalf of TCV to broader government sustainability initiatives, such as engagement with investor representative groups (e.g., PRI) or preparation of the State’s climate related risk disclosures.
Qualifications, Skills, and Experience

Relevant experience in sustainable finance or sustainability within a banking or wholesale financial services environment, ideally including sustainability reporting and disclosure;
Proven ability to build strong networks and maintain credibility and trust with internal and external stakeholders or clients at all levels;
Exceptional influencing, advocacy, and communication skills;
Strong attention to detail, coupled with excellent problem-solving and organisational abilities;
Solid understanding of wholesale financial market products;
Tertiary qualification in finance, economics, or sustainability is essential.
Why Join TCV
This is a rare opportunity to support the State of Victoria’s sustainable finance agenda and contribute to projects that deliver long-term value for the community.
  
Working closely with the Head of Sustainability, you’ll gain exposure to financial markets, and whole-of-government sustainability initiatives, while helping shape the continued evolution of TCV’s sustainable finance program.

